Bart Hughes has a pretty good life, a beautiful wife, a young son, a good
job with promotion prospects, and a renovated brownstone in New York. When
wife and kid leave for a vacation, Bart stays behind to work on a project

his basement has other plans for his time. Bart goes a bit bonkers trying
to kill this rat, destroying most of his house in the process. Certain
allegorical elements tie the household conflict to the rat race in his
office, but the main event is certainly the night-and-day contest of
wills between man and rodent.
